   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Year 28 of Marcus Aurelius Commodus Antoninus Augustus, Mecheir 11, for the account of Tybi. Paid by Petermouthis son of Kronion the son of Mystarion, his mother being Eudaimonis, for poll tax of year 27, for the Linypheion quarter, twenty dr., total 20, plus ten obols for supplementary fees.</ab>
